loadPtnPin(25.10)                                            loadPtnPin(25.10)

Name
       loadPtnPin - Loads either a partition floorplan file (from a saved par-
       tition design session) or a DEF file, and then displays the preassigned
       I/O pins for the partition

Syntax
       loadPtnPin

       [-help]

       [-report <string>]

       [-snapModifiedToBoundary]

       {-ptnName <string> | -all}

       {-file <string >| -def <string>}

       Loads  either a partition floorplan file (from a saved partition design
       session) or a DEF file, and then displays the preassigned I/O pins  for
       the  partition.  This command must be run for each partition in the de-
       sign. You can use this command on a partition design after loading  the
       top  level  floorplan  and  after  running/loading  placement and early
       global route data. Use unloadPtnPinto remove the preassigned I/O pins.

       Note: The loadPtnPin command can load partition files  that  are  saved
       using the saveFPlan command.

Parameters
       -all   Specifies  that  pin  positions for all the partitions should be
              loaded.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -def <string>
              Specifies the full pathname of the partition def file.

              Note: You can specify a DEF file in the gzip  format  (with  the
              .gz extension) also.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -file<string>
              Specifies the full path name of the partition floorplan file.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each loadPtnPin parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man loadPtnPin

       -ptnName <string>
              Specifies the name of the partition.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -report <string>
              Specifies the optional report filename that  contains  any  pins
              deleted or newly added.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -snapModifiedToBoundary
              Snaps  pins  to  the modified partition boundary. The pin is un-
              placed if it cannot be snapped to edge at same location in  same
              direction.  If the existing pin is off-grid, the loadPtnPin com-
              mand does not snap it to the track and you need to run  the  le-
              galizePin command to snap the pin to the track.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The  following  command  loads pin information from file EUG.fp.ptn for
       partition EUG

       loadPtnPin -ptnName EUG -file EUG.fp.ptn

